						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the central shrine in the temple of Avanāśiśvara.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīrarājēndradēva: Year 21 = 1227-28 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records the endowment of three <hi rend="italic">śalākai</hi> of <hi rend="italic">Śrīyakki achchu</hi> with the temple to provide for food-offerings during one <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> to the deity Kshētrapālappiḷḷaiyār by a certain Vīrapperumāḷ Edirilālādāṉ, a <hi rend="italic">Piḷḷai</hi> of the king.</p>						

						</summary>
